				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This was a tough one for me too. I was concerned with the low Quickness and Dexterity, and then the Bard becoming a meat shield, and going down way too much, or taking up too much mana to be healed and kept alive to help the group. A Bard just isn't any good in a group if it can not add much to it.
<br />

<br />
The concern I had was that the Strength is fine, but if you are slow dealing, it, you are gonna hit for x, and then miss three times before you hit for y, and then the same thing happens again. End result? Dead Bard ... or you better learn to play instruments fast and hope that the songs are not such high aggro that they allow you to live.
<br />

<br />
Right now, my main concern at 12 is that none of the song/spell lists are anywhere near what I'm getting ... and this means that Mythic is making way too many changes right now for us to be able to define where stats should go. I presume that the safe road at this time is "average" and hope that the Specializations help in the end ... which right now, they look like a bad joke.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
